description: FIGURES 65–71. Calapnita bidayuh sp. nov., SEM micrographs (ZFMK, Ar 15992–93). 65. Male prosoma, frontal view. 66. Male palpal tarsal organ. 67–68. Right procursus tip, retrolatero-ventral and retrolateral views (arrows point at distal spine-like process). 69. Split hair on procursus. 70. Tips of right appendix and embolus, retrolateral view. 71. Epigynum, ventral view. a, appendix; e, embolus. Scale lines: 10 µm (66, 69), 100 µm (65, 67, 68, 70, 71).
name: FIGURES 65–71 in Revision and cladistic analysis of the Southeast Asian leaf-dwelling spider genus Calapnita Simon (Araneae, Pholcidae)
